$ Graphviz (dot) examples

Some examples on how to use → tools/Graphviz.


{ Dotted edges etc

  This example uses a → tools/Graphviz/elems/edge[edge's] attribute `style` to draw a dotted edge.

  → tools/Graphviz/examples/dotted-edge.png

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/dotted-edge.dot||

}
{ Shape: record vs. plaintext

  If the → tools/Graphviz/attributes/shape[`shape` attribute] is set to `record`, the text (as controlled with the → tools/Graphviz/attributes/label[`label` attribute]) is layouted in tabular form.

  The vertical bar (`|`) starts a new row or column.

  The curly braces `{ ... }` change (flip) the direction of `|`.

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/img/shape-record-vs-plaintext.png||

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/shape-record-vs-plaintext.dot||

}
{ Multiple edges

  Normally, a dependency (an → tools/Graphviz/elems/edge) is declared with an arrow: `Node1 -> Node2`. Multiple → tools/Graphviz/elems/node[nodes] can be listed in curly braces, thus declaring multple edges in one go.

  → tools/Graphviz/examples/multiple-edges.png

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/multiple-edges.dot||

}
{ Left, mid and right aligned text

  `\l` makes the preceeding text right aligned, `\n` makes it centered and `\r` makes it left aligned.

  → tools/Graphviz/examples/left-mid-right-aligned-text.png

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/left-mid-right-aligned-text.dot||

}
{ Giving the graph a title

  With the → tools/Graphviz/attributes/label[`label` attribute], the graph can be given a *caption*:

  → tools/Graphviz/examples/label.png

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/label.dot||

}
{ HTML like labels

  If the text of → tools/Graphviz/attributes/label[`label`] is enclosed in `<…>` rather than in `"…"`, the text is treated as → development/web/HTML and rendered as
  → tools/Graphviz/attributes/label/HTML-like[HTML like label].

  → tools/Graphviz/examples/label-html-like.png

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/label-html-like.dot||

}
{ rank

  `{ rank=same node_1 node_2 … }` specifies that the specified nodes have the same rank, that is, that their distance from the top or left
  border is equal.

  → tools/Graphviz/examples/rank.png

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/rank.dot||

}
{ Subgraph (clusters)

  → tools/Graphviz/examples/subgraph.png

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/subgraph.dot||

}
{ Nested clusters

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/img/nested-clusters.png||

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/nested-clusters.dot||

}
{ HTML table

  HTML tables are produced if the value of the → tools/Graphviz/attributes/label[`label` attribute] is enclosed in `<…>` rather than `"…"`:
  → tools/Graphviz/examples/html-table.png

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/html-table.dot||
}
{ Nested HTML table

  HTML tables can be nested
  → tools/Graphviz/examples/html-table-nested.png

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/html-table-nested.dot||
}
{ Colors

  A color is specified with one of the → tools/Graphviz/attributes/_color[attributes that relate to colors].

  → tools/Graphviz/examples/colors.png

  gh|about-Graphviz|/examples/colors.dot||

}
